After the conversion is approved under subsection (2) of this section, the partnership or limited partnership shall file articles of organization with the office of the Secretary of State which satisfy the requirements of KRS 275.025 and include:
A statement that the partnership or limited partnership was converted to a limited liability company from a partnership or limited partnership, as the case may be;
Its former name;
In the case of a partnership, a statement of the number of votes cast by the partners entitled to vote for and against the conversion and, if the vote is less than unanimous, the number or percentage required to approve the conversion under the partnership agreement; and
If the converting partnership has filed a statement of registration as a limited liability partnership in accordance with KRS 362.555, a statement of qualification in accordance with KRS 362.1-931, or a statement of partnership authority, each shall be deemed canceled as of the effective date and time of the articles of organization as determined in accordance with KRS 275.020; and
In the case of a limited partnership, the converting limited partnership's certificate of limited partnership shall be deemed canceled as of the effective date and time of the articles of organization as determined in accordance with KRS 275.020.
